Section 1:
1 L.D. 129
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 STATE AND LOCAL GOVERNMENT
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 60, L.D. 129, “An Act to Amend the Law
10 Governing Dedimus Justices”
11 Amend the bill by inserting after the title and before the enacting clause the following:
12 'Emergency preamble. Whereas, acts and resolves of the Legislature do not
13 become effective until 90 days after adjournment unless enacted as emergencies; and
14 Whereas, the Governor may appoint in every county persons to be designated as
15 dedimus justices, before whom the oath required by the Constitution of Maine to qualify
16 civil officers may be taken and subscribed; and
17 Whereas, the need for the services that dedimus justices perform is outpacing the
18 number of dedimus justices who can be found to perform the duties of that commission;
19 and
20 Whereas, keeping an accurate account of how many people in this State are
21 commissioned as dedimus justices and how to contact them is critical information for
22 communities across this State who need the service that a dedimus justice performs; and
23 Whereas, this legislation must take effect before the end of the 90-day period to
24 immediately address the shortage of dedimus justices available to qualify civil officers in
25 the State; and
26 Whereas, in the judgment of the Legislature, these facts create an emergency within
27 the meaning of the Constitution of Maine and require the following legislation as
28 immediately necessary for the preservation of the public peace, health and safety; now,
29 therefore,'
30 Amend the bill by inserting after section 1 the following:
31 'Sec. 2. Mailing from Secretary of State. The Secretary of State shall send a
32 mailing to each person designated prior to October 1, 2025 as a dedimus justice pursuant
33 to the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 5, section 4 to request in return the person's updated
34 contact information, including the person's residence or mailing address, e-mail address
Page 1 - 132LR0560(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 60, L.D. 129
315 and telephone number. The mailing must also include information about the changes to
326 Title 5, section 4 provided in this Act and make clear that a dedimus justice designated
337 prior to October 1, 2025 is exempt from the term length requirement. Additionally, the
348 mailing must explain how the changes provide the opportunity for a dedimus justice to
359 resign the dedimus justice's commission.'
6 Amend the bill by adding before the summary the following:
7 'Emergency clause. In view of the emergency cited in the preamble, this legislation
8 takes effect when approved.'
9 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
10 number to read consecutively.
11 SUMMARY
1122 This amendment adds a section to the bill directing the Secretary of State to send a
1133 mailing to each person designated prior to October 1, 2025 as a dedimus justice pursuant
1144 to the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 5, section 4 to request in return the person's updated
1155 contact information, including the person's residence or mailing address, e-mail address
1166 and telephone number. It requires that the mailing must also include information about the
1177 changes to Title 5, section 4 provided in this legislation and make clear that a dedimus
1188 justice designated prior to October 1, 2025 is exempt from the term length requirement.
1199 Additionally, the mailing must explain how the changes provide the opportunity for a
2200 dedimus justice to resign the dedimus justice's commission.
2211 The amendment adds an emergency preamble and emergency clause.
2222 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
2233 (See attached)
Page 2 - 132LR0560(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
